SIMPLE: cohabitation
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cohabitation
<hw>Co*hab"i*ta"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>cohabitatio</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act or state of
dwelling together, or in the same place with another.</def>
<rj><au>Feltham.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>The living together of a man and
woman in supposed sexual relationship.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That the duty of <qex>cohabitation</qex> is released by the
cruelty of one of the parties is admitted.</q> <rj><qau>Lord
Stowell.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cohabiter</ent>⟦br⟧
